  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Montana is in a great location on the pedestrianised Corso Italia street running through <a data-udi="umb://document/2dcb1a3292da421780aa165d449493a9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2dcb1a3292da421780aa165d449493a9}" title="Cortina D’Ampezzo">Cortina</a>. It's a lovely little bed and breakfast and a great place to stay for skiers, and those wanting a more laid back holiday.</p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>With a great location along the main Corso Italia street, you are just a snowballs throw away from the Faloria lift, taking you up to the pretty Faloria-Cristallo Ski Area. The ski bus stop is close as well, so you can easily get onto the other ski areas including the Tofana Ski Area and the Falzarego Ski Area, linking Cortina with the rest of the extensive <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomites Ski Area</a>. It also means at the end of a great day's skiing there's no need to hurry back. Enjoy a few mountain drinks first and then it's just a short walk from the bus stop back to the comfort of the hotel.</p>
<p>The lovely Corso Italia street is home to some of the most <span>prestigious brands, and nestled between them you can find a range of sport shops, cosy cafes and historic buildings. When it comes to dinner, </span>head into the bustling streets where you'll be spoilt for choice with lots of great restaurants serving everything from traditional pizza to Michelin-starred cuisine.</p>]]></description>
